verbs.description: clubhaul (third-person singular simple present clubhauls, present participle clubhauling, simple past and past participle clubhauled)

entries.meaning: (transitive, nautical) To force (a sailing vessel) to change tack by dropping the lee-anchor and hauling in the anchor cable to swing the stern to windward.
